overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by integrating a database for response storage and developing an
  admin dashboard for data access. The primary goal was to enable the client to
  view and export questionnaire data. The agent evaluated the existing codebase,
  which already had the questionnaire logic and PDF generation, but lacked
  database integration and an admin interface. Key decisions involved using
  NeonDB (PostgreSQL) for the database, implementing a simple password-based
  authentication system, and updating the demographic data collected to include
  year of birth and sex while retaining existing fields. The implementation
  involved updating Prisma schema, creating API endpoints for data submission,
  retrieval, and CSV export, and building a client-side admin dashboard with
  login functionality. All specified tasks were successfully completed.
